    <h1>Lower Prices That Last for you this fes&#xAD;tive sea&#xAD;son</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201228/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-28"><time>2020-12-28</time></a>
        - <span>SINGAPORE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Gi­ant’s Lower Prices That Last cam­paign is here to spice up your fes­tive meals with the fresh­est pro­duce while keep­ing prices af­ford­able. While you pre­pare for your New Year and Chi­nese New Year meals, give their star prod­ucts a try!</p>
    <p>Pro­mo­tional items in­clude Golden Pom­fret at $6 for two, Van­namei prawns at $1 for 100g, minced pork at $0.90 for 100g, Mead­ows fresh milk at $2 for 1-litre and Fuji ap­ples at $2.50 for five.</p>
    <p>In Septem­ber, Gi­ant an­nounced an in­vest­ment of $17 mil­lion in the Lower Prices That Last cam­paign to re­duce the prices of hun­dreds of ev­ery­day es­sen­tials, and has been do­ing so con­sis­tently for more than 100 days since the launch. Gi­ant will con­tinue to hold down th­ese prices for months to come to align with their be­lief that it’s the lit­tle things that make a Gi­ant dif­fer­ence.</p>

